// Blueprint Class: BP_CharacterManager
// Parent Class: Actor
// Description: Manages character spawning and variation system

/*
This Blueprint implements the Character Manager that interfaces with the C++ Character System.
It handles:
- MetaHuman asset loading and management
- Character spawning with procedural variations
- Character database management
- Integration with the narrative system

Key Components:
1. Character System Component (C++)
2. MetaHuman Asset Arrays
3. Character Database DataTable
4. Spawn Location Management

Blueprint Graph Logic:

Event BeginPlay:
- Initialize MetaHuman assets
- Load character database
- Set up spawn locations

Function: SpawnRandomCharacter(Archetype, Location)
- Generate random character data via C++ system
- Spawn MetaHuman at location
- Apply variations
- Register character in scene

Function: SpawnNamedCharacter(CharacterName, Location)
- Look up character in database
- Spawn specific character
- Apply stored variations

Function: GetAvailableCharacters(Archetype)
- Query character database
- Return filtered list

Variables:
- MetaHumanMaleAssets: Array of SkeletalMesh
- MetaHumanFemaleAssets: Array of SkeletalMesh
- CharacterDatabase: DataTable
- SpawnedCharacters: Map of Character references
- MaxCharactersInScene: Integer (default 50)

This Blueprint serves as the main interface between the game world and the character system,
ensuring proper MetaHuman integration and performance management.
*/